cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with geolocating images on a 2-D map, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions learning a low dimensional embedded space, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The approach involves comparing images with local neighbourhoods of the map, which involves graph theory and computational geometry, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under the category of multimedia (MM), making cs.MM a possible sub-category as well.
